2014.09.01
README file for Zenon Modulo v 0.2.1

----------------------------------------

For license information, see LICENSE
For install information, see INSTALL

----------------------------------------

Remarks:

- Special unofficial release fo BWare project (development version)

- Uses TPTP TFF1 input format only

- Zenon Modulo is an automated theorem prover for classical
  first order logic

- Zenon Modulo is part of the BWare project
  http://bware.lri.fr/

- Proceedings about Zenon Modulo may be found here
  http://hal.inria.fr/hal-00909784
  http://hal.inria.fr/hal-00909688

- Zenon Modulo accepts input files with the TPTP syntax 
  http://www.cs.miami.edu/~tptp/

- Zenon Modulo may produce proof certificats for Dedukti
  https://www.rocq.inria.fr/deducteam/Dedukti/


----------------------------------------

Examples:

- Run Zenon Modulo to the TPTP file problem.p with TFF1 syntax
  # zenon_modulo -itptp -b-rwrt /path/to/file/problem.p


WARNING: use only with TPTP TFF1 files produces by why3 with 
         B_modulo.why as the library input file